<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Find the area of a triangle with sides <m>{6}</m> cm and <m>{5}</m> cm and included angle <m>{45}</m>°.
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>2 decimal places</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text{cm}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Use the formula:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = \frac{1}{2}ab\sin C
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Substitute the values:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = \frac{1}{2} \times {6} \times {5} \times \sin {45}^\circ
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Evaluate:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {10.61}\text{ cm}^2
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>10.61</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>